data.title: Art, Events & Community
data.meta_description: Enjoy exhibitions & CAM's collection, plus events for all ages. General admission is always free. Open late Thursdays.
data.text:
Closing Soon – From Shanghai to Ohio: Woo Chong Yung (1898–1989)

May 10–August 18, 2024

From the 1920s to 1949, Woo was at the center of China’s cultural world, recognized in the art circles of both Shanghai and Beijing. Free.

Learn More »

The Culture: Hip Hop and Contemporary Art in the 21st Century

June 28–September 29, 2024

The Culture showcases more than 100 works of art by some of today’s most important and celebrated artists and fashion brands

Learn More »

Rodin | Response: FIELD family secrets

June 14–September 8, 2024

What do an Egyptian mirror from 2000 BCE, a bronze statue conceived in France in the 1880s, and a 2024 bio-sculpture composed from lawn waste have in common?

Learn More »

Coming Soon – Discovering Ansel Adams

September 27, 2024–January 19, 2025

Premiering at the Cincinnati Art Museum, Discovering Ansel Adams provides an unprecedented exploration of the early career of Ansel Adams (1902–1984), demonstrating how, between 1916 and the 1940s, Adams developed from a 14-year-old tourist with a camera into America’s most celebrated photographer.

Learn More »

Coming Soon – George Bellows: American Life in Print

October 25, 2024–February 9, 2025

During his 20-year career, his paintings captured the spirit and character of life in the first quarter of the twentieth century.

Learn More »
